Opposition leader Raila Odinga likened Tarbaj MP Mohamed Elmi and his Eldas counterpart Aden Keynan to ticks sticking to a cow being slaughtered.The two defected from ODM.Raila, who was addressing NASA supporters in Wajir Stadium on Saturday, accused the two, who were elected on the ODM ticket, of going to bed with the enemy &mdash; Jubilee Party.The two politicians led a team of elders and their supporters from the Degodia community to State House, where they announced that they were decamping from ODM and would support President Uhuru Kenyatta&rsquo;s reelection.Their decision to join the ruling party had been informed by the development agenda implemented by the government throughout the county.But Raila disputed this, and instead hipped praised on Governor Ahmed Abdullahi, whom he said had initiated many development projects across the county despite the meagre resources allocated to him by the national government.&ldquo;It&rsquo;s unfortunate that our good friends who we have walked with in the journey all along have decided to dance and dine with our enemies,&rdquo; he said.&ldquo;They are joining Jubilee, but little do they know that we are taking Jubilee to the slaughterhouse.&rdquo;Raila, who was with Kalonzo Musyoka, Mosses Wetang&rsquo;ula and Musalia Mudavadi, said the two MPs have benefited from the opposition party by holding positions in Parliament. Mudavadi said NASA will win the President contest on August 8.Kalonzo said National Assembly majority leader Aden Duale has frustrated efforts to have the Truth Justice and Reconciliation Commission Report tabled in Parliament.The commission was set up in 2008 to probe the 2007-08 post-election violence.